
  <sn><md>### Profit {.text-center}

Farida Begum decided to deposit her savings in a bank. She deposited Tk. 10,000 in a bank. After one year, she went to the bank to take a bank statement. She noticed that her deposited amount had been increased by Tk. 700 and her balance became Tk. 10,700.

![diagram](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nh-em0n/QDoc/main/BCS/Math/Simple%20and%20Compound%20Profits/Assets/How_bank_works_diagram.png)


++How was the amount of money of Farida Begum increased by Tk. 700?++

When money is deposited in a bank, the bank invests that money as loans in different sectors, such as business, house-building, etc., and gets profit from those sectors. From that profit, the bank gives some money to the depositor. This money is the **profit** of the depositor.

The money which was first deposited in the bank is her **principal amount**. To deposit or give money as a loan and to take money from anyone as a loan is accomplished by a process. This process relates to the **principal**, the **rate of profit**, **time**, and **profit**.
</md></sn>
